Hello Rafaella,
Responding to your email below.
I understand that David has responded to acknowledge that there are more co=
ntents to schedule and appraise and he is continuing to do so.
You have sked me for Towers approval for you to appoint a Structural Engine=
er to assess the property. There is no requirement for this to be done. As =
explained in my previous email =E2=80=93 we have attended with a technical =
building Consultant who is well qualified to make the necessary observation=
s and issue documents and instructions on the repairs that are required to =
complete repairs to your home. I have copied the capability statement direc=
tly below which I shared with you last night. Noting that ASURNZ will refer=
 to a CPEng qualified structural engineer only if required after having com=
pleted their report. We will of course share the report we receive from ASU=
RNZ with you.
To that end Tower will not engage a CPEng qualified structural engineer, un=
til instructed to do so by ASURNZ. Tower will not be obliged to reimburse y=
ou if you chose to do this for yourself.

I have included an extract below from your policy wording which explains th=
e policy response position on this issue. Of most relevance here is the pre=
facing wording which states that: =E2=80=98 We will pay where necessary =E2=
=80=98. Please refer to policy wording extract below.
I have also attached a copy of the full policy wording for your further ref=
erence.

Further, considering the knowledge and experience provided by ASURNZ person=
nel regarding the assessment of fire damaged timber framed buildings, inclu=
ding my knowledge and experience, I doubt there would be any additional ben=
efit gained by engaging a structural engineer for this claim.  However, sho=
uld any design requirements that sit outside the scope limitations of NZS 3=
604:2011 and that require specific engineering design become apparent durin=
g scoping of repairs, I confirm that we will in that instance seek engineer=
ing design from a suitably experienced Chartered Professional Engineer (CPE=
ng).

[cid:image001.png@01DC0C58.C876DA80]

I would like to carry on with our provided process and have the upstairs cl=
eaned and the gib-board wall linings removed to enable us to inspect the ex=
terior wall cavities to complete a thorough assessment of the repairs requi=
red. Can I have your approval to instruct Davids team to do so?

Best Regards,
Grant.

[cid:image002.png@01DC0C58.C876DA80]
Grant Metson
Regional Manager - House Assessing
Phone 021 744 288
Level 5, 136 Fanshawe Street,
PO Box 90347, Auckland 1142

