Hi Grant, Yes =E2=80=93 David=E2=80=99s team can commence cleaning of the m=
id-floor level tomorrow, strictly on the basis that this work is limited to=
 what is necessary to allow full assessment of the damage and to determine =
the scope and cost of repair works,
Hi Grant,

Yes =E2=80=93 David=E2=80=99s team can commence cleaning of the mid-floor l=
evel tomorrow, strictly on the basis that this work is limited to what is n=
ecessary to allow full assessment of the damage and to determine the scope =
and cost of repair works, and will not remove, cover, or alter any areas th=
at still require inspection for damage, safety, or compliance purposes. Ack=
nowledged and agreed =E2=80=93 Davids team will complete cleaning only. Poi=
nt of clarification =E2=80=93 I need them to remove target areas of wall li=
nings so we can continue to determine the resulting damage. So in doing thi=
s =E2=80=93 they are enabling us to continue with correct and ongoing asses=
sment, as we cannot inspect the wall cavity in targeted areas with wall lin=
ings in place.

In particular, can we please also arrange to assess the roof and the gas un=
it as part of this stage, so that any issues are identified before assessin=
g the damage and determining the scope and cost of repair works? Agreed and=
 acknowledged. We did access the roof space during our visit yesterday and =
I will enlist the services of the service contractor to make a formal asses=
sment of the gas exchange unit. They are the specialist provider on this un=
it =E2=80=93 so I will seek their professional advice on the next steps req=
uired to include this unit in the assessment.

Regarding contents, there is still a substantial amount to go through both =
upstairs and downstairs. Could you please confirm what the plan and timelin=
e are for completing the contents assessment? I understand that the downsta=
irs will be complete by now. I will have David comment further on this subj=
ect.

Lastly, I would like to engage a structural engineer for damage assessment.=
 As requested in my 1 July email, please confirm whether Tower requires pri=
or approval for this, and provide the relevant policy guidelines or procedu=
res for reimbursement of claims preparation work.
Tower Insurance will not need to engage a CPEng to determine repair details=
. Stephen walker will complete the structural detailing required to determi=
ne the framing repairs to the dwelling as this is within the scope limitati=
ons of the Standard NZS 3604:2011.
The engagement of ASURNZ to provide this report and the details required to=
 complete the repairs is at Towers own cost.
Stephen Walker has provided the following statement and has also provided t=
he attached qualifications and capability statements for your reference:

Hi Grant,

Please see attached as requested.  I have also included copy of our legisla=
tive and regulatory capability statement.

Note that this building is within the scope limitations of the Standard NZS=
 3604:2011.  NZS 3604:2011 is a cited means of compliance with building cod=
e clause B1 =E2=80=93 Structure for timber framed buildings not requiring s=
pecific engineering design.  This means that there is no legislative requir=
ement for engaging a structural engineer for design requirements for the re=
pair of this building.  As such, any repair or construction carried out in =
accordance with the Standard is deemed to satisfy the relevant provisions o=
f the building code and the Building Act 2004.

Further, considering the knowledge and experience provided by ASURNZ person=
nel regarding the assessment of fire damaged timber framed buildings, inclu=
ding my knowledge and experience, I doubt there would be any additional ben=
efit gained by engaging a structural engineer for this claim.  However, sho=
uld any design requirements that sit outside the scope limitations of NZS 3=
604:2011 and that require specific engineering design become apparent durin=
g scoping of repairs, I confirm that we will in that instance seek engineer=
ing design from a suitably experienced Chartered Professional Engineer (CPE=
ng).

Kind regards,

Stephen Walker
Principal Consultant

<image003.jpg>


My consent to this cleaning is given strictly on the basis that it is for a=
ssessment purposes only, does not waive any of my rights under the policy, =
the Fair Insurance Code, or applicable New Zealand laws, and that no repair=
 or reinstatement work will proceed until these assessments are complete an=
d we have agreed the scope and cost. Agreed and acknowledged.

Kind regards,
Raffaella

