Subject: 23 Mays Road, Devonport - C90306048 - Repair Scoping - 12:30 today

Good morning Rafaella,
As per the next phase of the process map =E2=80=93 Stephen Walker from ASUR=
NZ =E2=80=93 our Technical Building Consultant is due to visit site and aut=
hor the scope of works required.
Stephen and I will be visiting site at 12:30 today to complete the walk-thr=
ough and determine the scope-of-works for the repairs to your home.
Once we have completed this document =E2=80=93 I can return and go through =
each item on the scope line-by-line in detail with you so you can gain the =
confidence that we have captured everything.
When we go through the scope together =E2=80=93 we can consider adding anyt=
hing further that is necessary if we need to. I am exceptionally confident =
that Stephen and I will capture everything on the first draft =E2=80=93 but=
 I want you to know that you will sign-off on the scope-of-works as being c=
omplete before we move to the repair phase.
You do not need to join us for today=E2=80=99s visit =E2=80=93 but you are =
more than welcome to if you wish. As I stated =E2=80=93 we can review it to=
gether once complete. I will let you decide whether you wish to join us or =
not.
Please do not hesitate to contact me if you have any questions or concerns =
at all.
Many Thanks,
Grant.

