<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">I understand that D=
avid has responded to acknowledge that there are more contents to schedule =
and appraise and he is continuing to do so.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">You have sked me fo=
r Towers approval for you to appoint a Structural Engineer to assess the pr=
operty. There is no requirement for this to be done. As explained in my pre=
vious email =E2=80=93 we have attended with
 a technical building Consultant who is well qualified to make the necessar=
y observations and issue documents and instructions on the repairs that are=
 required to complete repairs to your home. I have copied the capability st=
atement directly below which I shared
 with you last night. Noting that ASURNZ will refer to a CPEng qualified st=
ructural engineer only if required after having completed their report. We =
will of course share the report we receive from ASURNZ with you.<o:p></o:p>=
</span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">To that end Tower w=
ill not engage a CPEng qualified structural engineer, until instructed to d=
o so by ASURNZ.
<u>Tower will not be obliged to reimburse you if you chose to do this for y=
ourself.</u>
<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></=
span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">I have included an =
extract below from your policy wording which explains the policy response p=
osition on this issue. Of most relevance here is the prefacing wording whic=
h states that: =E2=80=98 We will pay where necessary
 =E2=80=98. Please refer to policy wording extract below.<o:p></o:p></span>=
</p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">I have also attache=
d a copy of the full policy wording for your further reference. &nbsp;<o:p>=
</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></=
span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:#275317;mso-fareast-language:EN-U=
S">Further, considering the knowledge and experience provided by ASURNZ per=
sonnel regarding the assessment of fire damaged
 timber framed buildings, including my knowledge and experience, I doubt th=
ere would be any additional benefit gained by engaging a structural enginee=
r for this claim.&nbsp; However, should any design requirements that sit ou=
tside the scope limitations of NZS 3604:2011
 and that require specific engineering design become apparent during scopin=
g of repairs, I confirm that we will in that instance seek engineering desi=
gn from a suitably experienced Chartered Professional Engineer (CPEng).</sp=
an><o:p></o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt"><o:p=
>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
