ont-size:1.0pt;color:white">Hi Grant, Yes =E2=80=93 David=E2=80=99s team ca=
n commence cleaning of the mid-floor level tomorrow, strictly on the basis =
that this work is limited to what is necessary to allow
 full assessment of the damage and to determine the scope and cost of repai=
r works,</span><o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">Hi Grant,<o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">Yes =E2=80=93 David=E2=80=99s team can commence clea=
ning of the mid-floor level tomorrow, strictly on the basis that this work =
is limited to what is necessary to allow full assessment of the damage and =
to determine the scope and cost of repair works, and
 will not remove, cover, or alter any areas that still require inspection f=
or damage, safety, or compliance purposes.
<span style=3D"color:#0070C0">Acknowledged and agreed =E2=80=93 Davids team=
 will complete cleaning only. Point of clarification =E2=80=93 I need them =
to remove target areas of wall linings so we can continue to determine the =
resulting damage. So in doing this =E2=80=93 they are enabling
 us to continue with correct and ongoing assessment, as we cannot inspect t=
he wall cavity in targeted areas with wall linings in place. &nbsp;</span><=
o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">In particular, can we please also arrange to assess =
the roof and the gas unit as part of this stage, so that any issues are ide=
ntified before assessing the damage and determining the scope and cost of r=
epair works?
<span style=3D"color:#0070C0">Agreed and acknowledged. We did access the ro=
of space during our visit yesterday and I will enlist the services of the s=
ervice contractor to make a formal assessment of the gas exchange unit. The=
y are the specialist provider on this
 unit =E2=80=93 so I will seek their professional advice on the next steps =
required to include this unit in the assessment. &nbsp;&nbsp;</span><o:p></=
o:p></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">Regarding contents, there is still a substantial amo=
unt to go through both upstairs and downstairs. Could you please confirm wh=
at the plan and timeline are for completing the contents assessment?
<span style=3D"color:#0070C0">I understand that the downstairs will be comp=
lete by now. I will have David comment further on this subject.</span><o:p>=
</o:p></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">Lastly, I would like to engage a structural engineer=
 for damage assessment. As requested in my 1 July email, please confirm whe=
ther Tower requires prior approval for this, and provide the relevant polic=
y guidelines or procedures for reimbursement
 of claims preparation work. <o:p></o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;Aptos Display&quot;=
,sans-serif;color:#0070C0">Tower Insurance will not need to engage a CPEng =
to determine repair details. Stephen walker will complete the structural de=
tailing required to determine the framing repairs
 to the dwelling as this is within the scope limitations of the </span><spa=
n lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-family:&quot;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif;=
color:#0070C0;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">Standard NZS 3604:2011.</span><o:=
p></o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-family:&quot;Apto=
s Display&quot;,sans-serif;color:#0070C0;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">The en=
gagement of ASURNZ to provide this report and the details required to compl=
ete the repairs is at Towers own cost.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;Aptos Display&quot;=
,sans-serif;color:#0070C0">Stephen Walker has provided the following statem=
ent and has also provided the attached qualifications and capability statem=
ents for your reference:</span><o:p></o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:#275317;mso-fareast-language:EN-U=
S">&nbsp;</span><o:p></o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:#275317;mso-fareast-language:EN-U=
S">Hi Grant,</span><o:p></o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:#275317;mso-fareast-language:EN-U=
S">&nbsp;</span><o:p></o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:#275317;mso-fareast-language:EN-U=
S">Please see attached as requested.&nbsp; I have also included copy of our=
 legislative and regulatory capability statement.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:#275317;mso-fareast-language:EN-U=
S">&nbsp;</span><o:p></o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:#275317;mso-fareast-language:EN-U=
S">Note that this building is within the scope limitations of the Standard =
NZS 3604:2011.&nbsp; NZS 3604:2011 is a cited means of
 compliance with building code clause B1 =E2=80=93 Structure for timber fra=
med buildings not requiring specific engineering design.&nbsp; This means t=
hat there is no legislative requirement for engaging a structural engineer =
for design requirements for the repair of this
 building.&nbsp; As such, any repair or construction carried out in accorda=
nce with the Standard is deemed to satisfy the relevant provisions of the b=
uilding code and the Building Act 2004.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:#275317;mso-fareast-language:EN-U=
S">&nbsp;</span><o:p></o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:#275317;mso-fareast-language:EN-U=
S">Further, considering the knowledge and experience provided by ASURNZ per=
sonnel regarding the assessment of fire damaged
 timber framed buildings, including my knowledge and experience, I doubt th=
ere would be any additional benefit gained by engaging a structural enginee=
r for this claim.&nbsp; However, should any design requirements that sit ou=
tside the scope limitations of NZS 3604:2011
 and that require specific engineering design become apparent during scopin=
g of repairs, I confirm that we will in that instance seek engineering desi=
gn from a suitably experienced Chartered Professional Engineer (CPEng).</sp=
an><o:p></o:p></p>
